th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">the greatest business model</a> of the 2010s venture capit=
al=C2=A0boom. The model was:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padd=
ing-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You p=
aid MoviePass $10 a month.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In exch=
ange, you could see as many movies as you wanted, in theaters.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">MoviePass had no particular deals with the mov=
ie theaters; it just went out and bought whatever tickets you wanted at ret=
ail prices.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The retail price for a=
 movie ticket was about $10.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>If you saw more than one movie a month =E2=80=94=C2=A0as you probably did,=
 if you bothered to sign up for this service =E2=80=94=C2=A0MoviePass lost =
money on you.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But MoviePass =
supposedly collected data! Data is valuable! I don=E2=80=99t know.</li></ol=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This all worked out extremely poorly, as you=
=E2=80=99d expect =E2=80=94=C2=A0MoviePass <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/24088975.258366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnByLm9yZy8yMDE5Lz=
