-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> discussed at the time</a>:=C2=A0</p><blockquote><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Per Lowe's orders, MoviePass began limiting subscri=
ber access ahead of the April release of the highly anticipated "Avengers: =
Infinity War," according to multiple former employees. They said Lowe order=
ed that the passwords of a small percentage of power users be changed, prev=
enting them from logging onto the app and ordering tickets.</p></blockquote=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So part of me admires the gumption, sure, but=
 that seems like =E2=80=A6=C2=A0super-duper fraud?=C2=A0But here=E2=80=99s =
a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24088975.258366/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnRjLmdvdi9uZXdzLWV2ZW50cy9wcmVzcy1yZWxlYXNlcy8yMDIxLzA2L29=
wZXJhdG9ycy1tb3ZpZXBhc3Mtc3Vic2NyaXB0aW9uLXNlcnZpY2UtYWdyZWUtc2V0dGxlLWZ0Yw=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7b5500f5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">U.S. Federal Trade Commission action</a> from yes=
terday:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The operators of the Mo=
viePass subscription service have agreed to settle Federal Trade Commission=
 allegations they took steps to block subscribers from using the service as=
 advertised, while also failing to secure subscribers=E2=80=99 personal dat=
a.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Under the proposed settlement, MoviePass=
, Inc., its parent company Helios and Matheson Analytics, Inc. (Helios), an=
d their principals, Mitchell Lowe and Theodore Farnsworth, will be barred f=
rom misrepresenting their business and data security practices. In addition=
, any businesses controlled by MoviePass, Helios, or Lowe must implement co=
mprehensive information security programs.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
=E2=80=9CMoviePass and its executives went to great lengths to deny consume=
rs access to the service they paid for while also failing to secure their p=
ersonal information,=E2=80=9D said Daniel Kaufman, the FTC=E2=80=99s Acting=
 Director of the Bureau of Consumer Protection. =E2=80=9CThe FTC will conti=
nue working to protect consumers from deception and to ensure that business=
es deliver on their promises.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In i=
ts complaint, the FTC alleges that MoviePass, Inc.=E2=80=94along with its C=
EO, Lowe, as well as Helios and Farnsworth, CEO of Helios=E2=80=94deceptive=
ly marketed its =E2=80=9Cone movie per day=E2=80=9D service promised to sub=
scribers who paid for its $9.95 monthly service. ...</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">According to the FTC, MoviePass=E2=80=99s operators invalidated s=
ubscriber passwords while falsely claiming to have detected =E2=80=9Csuspic=
ious activity or potential fraud=E2=80=9D on the accounts. MoviePass's oper=
ators did this even though some of its own executives raised questions abou=
t the scheme, according to the complaint.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">They really changed people=E2=80=99s passwords so they couldn=
=E2=80=99t use the service, and their punishment is that they have to promi=
se not to do it again.=C2=A0The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/24088975.258366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnRjLmdvdi9zeXN0ZW0vZmlsZXMvZ=
G9jdW1lbnRzL2Nhc2VzLzE5Ml8zMDAwXy1fbW92aWVwYXNzX2NvbXBsYWludC5wZGY/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB6407fb53" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">complaint</a> is madness:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">Under Respondents=E2=80=99 password disruption program, Respond=
ents invalidated the passwords of the 75,000 subscribers who used the servi=
ce most frequently while claiming that =E2=80=9Cwe have detected suspicious=
 activity or potential fraud=E2=80=9D on the affected subscribers=E2=80=99 =
accounts. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The password disruption=
 program impeded subscribers=E2=80=99 ability to view movies because MovieP=
ass=E2=80=99s password reset process often failed. =E2=80=A6 Indeed, when d=
iscussing the password disruption program, a MoviePass executive acknowledg=
ed that subscribers using a common smartphone operating system would encoun=
ter technical difficulty in resetting their passwords.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">When subscribers attempted to contact MoviePass=E2=80=99s custo=
mer service about their inability to reset their MoviePass passwords, Respo=
ndents often responded weeks later or not at all.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They had formal business meetings about this, whe=
re=C2=A0they discussed the pros and cons of hacking their users=E2=80=99 ac=
counts:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On April 11, 2018, an e=
mployee of Respondent Helios, writing from Farnsworth=E2=80=99s personal em=
ail address and expressly =E2=80=9Con behalf of Ted [Farnsworth]=E2=80=9D t=
o Lowe and others, proposed a notice that informed subscribers that their a=
ccount passwords were required to be reset due to =E2=80=9Csuspicious activ=
ity or potential fraud.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Lowe circu=
lated the proposed notice to MoviePass executives for comment and personall=
y ordered subscribers=E2=80=99 passwords to be disrupted in accordance with=
 this plan. Lowe also personally chose the number of consumers who would be=
 affected by the program. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Lo=
we and Farnsworth presented the disruption program to other executives of R=
espondent MoviePass, one executive warned that the password disruption prog=
ram =E2=80=9Cwould be targeting all of our heavy users=E2=80=9D and that =
=E2=80=9C<strong>there is a high risk this would catch the FTC=E2=80=99s at=
tention (and State AG=E2=80=99s attention) </strong>and could reinvigorate =
their questioning of MoviePass, this time from a Consumer Protection standp=
oint.=E2=80=9D (Emphasis in original).</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anot=
her executive agreed, warning of =E2=80=9C<strong>FTC Fears</strong>: All [=
the other MoviePass executive=E2=80=99s] notes about FTC and PR [public rel=
ations] fire are my main concerns as I think the PR backlash will flame the=
 FTC stuff.=E2=80=9D (Emphasis in original).</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">In response to these concerns, Lowe responded, =E2=80=9COk I get it. So l=
et[=E2=80=99]s try this with a small group. Let[=E2=80=99]s say 2% of our h=
ighest volume users.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Respond=
ents MoviePass and Lowe tracked the effect of password disruption on subscr=
ibers=E2=80=99 use of the service. For example, Respondents MoviePass and L=
owe found that only one-half of affected subscribers had successfully reset=
 their passwords one week after they executed their plan.=C2=A0</p></blockq=
uote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bizarrely, MoviePass settled without payi=
ng a fine =E2=80=94=C2=A0apparently due to a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/24088975.258366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2NvdHVzYmxvZy5j=
b20vY2FzZS1maWxlcy9jYXNlcy9hbWctY2FwaXRhbC1tYW5hZ2VtZW50LWxsYy12LWZlZGVyYWw=
tdHJhZGUtY29tbWlzc2lvbi8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB422b0bc2" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: n=
one !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bor=
der-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">recent Supreme Court deci=
sion</a>=C2=A0limiting the FTC=E2=80=99s ability to extract money for stuff=
 like this =E2=80=94=C2=A0and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/24088975.258366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnRjLmdvdi9zeXN0ZW0vZmlsZXMvZG9=
jdW1lbnRzL3B1YmxpY19zdGF0ZW1lbnRzLzE1OTA3MTIvbW92aWVwYXNzX3N0YXRlbWVudF9waG=
lsbGlwc19maW5hbC5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5f5aac9e" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">one FTC commissioner dissent=
ed</a> even from making them promise not to do it again.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">Coincidentally, today Kevin Roose <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24088975.258366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb=
20vMjAyMS8wNi8wOC90ZWNobm9sb2d5L2ZhcmV3ZWxsLW1pbGxlbm5pYWwtbGlmZXN0eWxlLXN1=
YnNpZHkuaHRtbD9yZWZlcnJpbmdTb3VyY2U9YXJ0aWNsZVNoYXJl/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
